## 2. System Architecture & Data Flow

The program must process an incoming video stream frame-by-frame using a deterministic state-machine architecture.

```
+--------------------+      +-------------------------+      +-------------------------+
| Video Frame Stream | ---> |  Decoupled CV Trackers  | ---> |   Temporal FIFO Queues  |
+--------------------+      | (Independent CSRT Core) |      | (Maxlen=60 Ball / Foot) |
                            +-------------------------+      +-------------------------+
                                                                          |
+--------------------+      +-------------------------+                   |
| UI Display Overlay | <--- | Tactical Classification | <-----------------+
| & Final Data Dump  |      |   & Lens De-rotation    |
+--------------------+      +-------------------------+

```

### 2.1 State Management Components

* **Asset Queues:** Dual historical tracking registers implemented via `collections.deque(maxlen=60)`.
* `ball_points`: Tracks coordinate tuples `(x, y)` of the ball center.
* `foot_points`: Tracks coordinate tuples `(x, y)` of the foot center.
* `ball_widths`: Tracks structural tracking box widths `(w)` to evaluate real-time Z-depth.


* **Anchor Cache Engine:** Upon user initialization at `STRIKE_APPROACH_FRAME`, the system must cache the very first valid ball width value as a immutable baseline reference variable: `w_strike`.

