## 4. Analytical Classification Parameters

Once $\theta_{\text{final}}$ is safely calculated, the engine must evaluate and assign tactical shot signatures according to the following explicit geometric boundaries:

| Calculated Launch Angle Range ($\theta_{\text{final}}$) | Tactical Signature Designation |
| --- | --- |
| $\theta_{\text{final}} < 12.0^\circ$ | Low Driven / Power Shot |
| $12.0^\circ \le \theta_{\text{final}} \le 30.0^\circ$ | Long Ball / Driven Cross |
| $\theta_{\text{final}} > 30.0^\circ$ | Chip / Lob / Floating Cross |

